                    <p>“Liquidation Level” means the LTV Ratio (in the case of Cross Collateral Services) or the level (in the case of Futures trading services in general) as prescribed by Hasla from time to time in the Futures Trading Rules (as defined below) which will result in Hasla selling or disposing of any or all Collateral (in the case of Cross Collateral Services) or Margin (in the case of Futures trading services in general) in the applicable Futures Account(s) to satisfy the LTV Ratio or margin requirements (as the case may be).</p>
                    <p>“Liquidation Price” means the Mark Price at which Liquidation (as defined below) occurs. For the avoidance of doubt, the Liquidation Price as quoted by Hasla on its website or mobile application is for reference only and shall not be binding on Hasla.</p>
