                    <h3>3. Futures Orders</h3>
                    <p>3.1. To enter in to or close or otherwise carry out a Transaction, you may do so by placing a relevant Order with Hasla through the use of any Electronic Facility as Hasla may approve in its sole discretion.</p>
                    <p>3.2. In the event that Hasla assumes the role of the counterparty to any Transaction, Hasla shall be entitled to all gains, profits and benefits derived from such Transaction.</p>
                    <p>3.3. Nothing in this Agreement obliges Hasla to enter into any Transaction with you, and Hasla may refuse to enter into any Transaction, accept or otherwise act on any Order without giving any reason or any notice to you. Hasla shall be entitled (but not obliged) to verify and be satisfied with respect to the identity of the person purporting to give such Order or the source and origin of such Order and Hasla may rely or act upon any such Order unless and until Hasla is satisfied as to the matters on which Hasla sought verification.</p>
                    <p>3.4. Where any Order is ambiguous or inconsistent with any other Order, Hasla shall be entitled to rely and act upon any Order in accordance with any reasonable interpretation thereof which Hasla believes in good faith to be the correct interpretation.</p>
                    <p>3.5. Hasla shall only act on Order in respect of any Hasla Account and Futures Account or any part of the Digital Assets and Digital Currencies held in such accounts. Hasla shall not be required to act in accordance with any Order which purports to dispose of or deal with any Digital Assets and/or Digital Currencies which are in fact not held in any Hasla Account and/or Futures Account.</p>
