                    <p>4.3. The value of any Margin shall be as determined by Hasla in its sole and absolute discretion.</p>
                    <p>4.4. Where applicable, you acknowledge and agree that separate Margin shall be provided by you in respect of each position as Hasla may require, and that the Margin in respect of each position shall be treated as separate for the purposes of this Agreement. Upon specific instructions provided by you, Hasla may (but is not obliged to) transfer all or part of the Margin held by Hasla for you in respect of any Futures Account to any other Hasla Account or to utilise such Margin for any purposes as required by you.</p>
                    <p>4.5. Hasla may establish margin requirements in respect of its margin trading services and such margin requirements will be set out in the Futures Trading Rules. Hasla may, in its sole and absolute discretion, with or without notice to you, vary the margin requirements for any Futures Account at any time and by any level, and may also stipulate that such margin requirements shall apply to existing positions as well as new positions in the Transactions affected by such change. Any written notice from Hasla stating that any such circumstance has arisen shall be deemed to be a conclusive determination of that event. You acknowledge that Binance may, in certain market conditions, effect an immediate change in Margin limits or levels and/or require additional Margin to be deposited immediately or within a specified period of time which may be less than 24 hours, and waives any right to object on the grounds that such requirement is unreasonable. No previous margin requirements shall set a precedent or bind Hasla.</p>
                    <p>4.6. If Hasla determines that additional Margin is required, you shall deposit with Hasla such additional Margin immediately upon demand, provided that, notwithstanding any such demand for additional Margin, Hasla may at any time exercise its rights under Clause 8 (Default and Termination). In making such determination in respect of the Margin provided for any Futures Account, Hasla shall not be required to take into consideration Margin held by Binance for you in respect of any other Futures Account.</p>
                    <p>4.7. You acknowledge that Margin may be held and used to secure the performance of your obligations as well as for such other purposes as the Applicable Laws may permit or stipulate for the Transactions traded.</p>
                    <p>4.8. All Margin shall be held by Hasla, notwithstanding any provision or instructions to the contrary, as continuing security and shall be subject to a general lien and right of set off in favour of Hasla for any and all of your obligations, liabilities or monies whatsoever at any time now or hereafter owing, due, incurred or payable by you to Hasla under this Agreement or otherwise, whether present or future, actual or contingent, solely or jointly or whether as principal or surety, and Hasla may realise any of your Margin as provided for in this Agreement.</p>
                    <p>4.9. Hasla shall be entitled to deposit, pledge, repledge, hypothecate, re-hypothecate, invest or loan any Margin in whatever form provided by Hasla or otherwise, and shall not be under any obligation to notify you of the same nor account to you for any interest, income or benefit that may be derived therefrom. No interest shall be paid on any type of Margin deposited by you with Hasla and you acknowledge and agree that interest earned on the Margin deposited under this Agreement may be retained by Hasla for its own account and benefit. Hasla shall at no time be required to deliver to you the identical property delivered to or purchased by Hasla as Margin for the Futures Account but only property of substantially the same kind and amount, subject to adjustments for quantity and quality variations at the market price prevailing at the time of such delivery. Hasla shall not be liable to you for the loss of any Margin resulting directly or indirectly from the closure, bankruptcy, insolvency, liquidation, receivership or other events of a similar nature of any broker, market association, or body with which the Margin is deposited or pledged.</p>
                    <p>4.10. You shall at your own cost and at Hasla ’s request, execute and do all such deeds, acts and things (including without limitation, the performance of such further acts or the execution and delivery of any additional instruments or documents) as Hasla may require for the purposes of this Agreement, including but not limited to perfecting Hasla ’s rights to the Margin provided by you.</p>
