                    <h3>5. Margin Level, Margin Call and Liquidation</h3>
                    <p>5.1. Without prejudice to the generality of this Clause 5 of this Agreement, unless otherwise directed by Hasla :</p>
                    <p>(a) You agree to place the required Initial Margin with Hasla before entering into any Transaction;</p>
                    <p>(b) You agree to maintain sufficient Maintenance Margin at all times for its outstanding Transactions. If the Margin falls below the required Maintenance Margin, you agree to transfer additional Margin to Hasla whether or not a Margin Call has been made by Hasla to restore to the required Initial Margin for the outstanding Transactions;</p>
                    <p>(c) You acknowledge that we calculate the profit and loss of your open positions in the Futures based on a proprietary model and that Hasla has the sole discretion to choose and amend the specification of the such proprietary model in order to reflect Hasla ’s view of the fair market price of the Futures;</p>
                    <p>(d) You acknowledge that if the margin requirements falls below the Liquidation Level such that the value of the Mark Price equals the value of the Liquidation Price, Hasla may and shall be fully entitled (but shall not be obliged) to sell or dispose of any or all Margins in your Futures Account in order to satisfy the margin requirements prescribed by Hasla for compliance by you, whether or not a Margin Call has been made (“Liquidation”), and Hasla is not required to provide notice before commencing Liquidation.</p>
                    <p>(e) You acknowledge and agree that it is your principal responsibility to monitor the margin requirements (including the Initial Margin, Maintenance Margin, the Mark Price and the Liquidation Price) in and for your Futures Account. All open positions of the Futures Account shall be marked-to-market daily, or at more frequent intervals as Hasla may determine in its sole discretion;</p>
                    <p>(f) Any Margin Call made by Hasla must be met by you by transferring additional Margin from your Hasla Account(s).</p>
                    <p>5.2. As Digital Asset markets are open 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, Margin Calls and liquidations may occur at any time, including outside of normal business hours. You further agree and acknowledge that the prices of Digital Assets are volatile and thus may decline speedily in value.</p>
                    <p>5.3. You acknowledge and agree that Hasla may (but shall not be obliged to) make Margin Calls on you in respect of any of your Futures Account orally or in writing or in such other manner as Hasla may in its sole and absolute discretion deem appropriate. Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, you acknowledge and agree that Hasla may contact you via telephone or email at any of the telephone number or email address provided by you to Hasla for the purposes of any Margin Calls and you shall make yourself available at such telephone numbers or email. If Hasla fails to reach you at any such telephone numbers or email, you shall be deemed to have defaulted on the Margin Call and Hasla may at any time exercise its rights set out in Clause 8 (Default and Termination). For the avoidance of doubt, Hasla shall be entitled (but not obliged) to make Margin Calls on you in respect of any of your Futures Account.</p>
                    <p>5.4. Failure of Hasla to exercise any or all of its rights under this Clause 5 shall not constitute a waiver of its rights to do so at any time thereafter, nor shall Hasla be subject to any liability to you for its acts or its failure to so act.</p>
