                    <p>6.22. Failure of Binance to exercise any or all of its rights under this Clause 6 shall not constitute a waiver of its rights to do so at any time thereafter, nor shall Hasla be subject to any liability to you for its acts or its failure to so act.</p>
                    <p>6.23. You acknowledge and agree that it is your sole responsibility to monitor the LTV Ratio requirements (including LTV Ratio) in and for your Futures Accounts. All open positions of your Futures Accounts shall be marked-to-market daily, or at more frequent intervals as Hasla may determine in its sole and absolute discretion.</p>
                    <p>6.24. Any Margin Call made by Hasla must be met by you by transferring additional Collateral from your Hasla Account(s).</p>
                    <p>6.25. You acknowledge and agree that Hasla may (but shall not be obliged to) make Margin Calls on you in respect of any of your Futures Account orally or in writing or in such other manner as Hasla may in its sole and absolute discretion deem appropriate. Without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing, you acknowledge and agree that Hasla may contact you via telephone or email at any of the telephone number or email address provided by you to Binance for the purposes of any Margin Calls and you shall make yourself available at such telephone numbers or email. If Binance fails to reach you at any such telephone numbers or email, you shall be deemed to have defaulted on the Margin Call and Hasla may at any time exercise its rights set out in Clause 8 (Default and Termination). For the avoidance of doubt, Hasla shall be entitled (but not obliged) to make Margin Calls on you in respect of any of your Futures Account.</p>
